    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for purchase is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving naturally aspirated mill delivers linear power through individual throttle bodies and is mated to a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. The chassis maintains its composure via a factory-equipped M-Variable differential lock and has been proactively addressed with rear subframe reinforcement plates. Suspension geometry remains true, providing the tactile feedback and turn-in precision characteristic of the E46 platform. While showing minor signs of use consistent with its age, the mechanical integrity is robust, with the Double VANOS system functioning within factory tolerances. This is a mechanically sound example ready for the enthusiast who values longitudinal dynamics and visceral throttle response.",
